4. Grafana Dashboard Configuration
Once Grafana is running, go to http://<your-domain>:3001 (e.g., http://grafana.barnabo-connect.com:3001).

Log in using admin/your-admin-password.

Add Prometheus as a data source in Grafana.

Go to Configuration (the gear icon) -> Data Sources -> Add data source -> Prometheus.

In the URL field, enter http://prometheus:9090.

5. Create Grafana Dashboards
Create custom dashboards to monitor key metrics like:

Container CPU/memory usage

HTTP request/response counts

Database query times

Custom metrics (like dungeon loading times)
